<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441381>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Acanthococcus coccineus (Cockerell 1894), first-instar nymph, The Bronx, Bronx County, New York, USA, August 31, 1944, on Mammillaria sp. and Harrisia sp., G. Rau. A=enlarged seta; C=7-locular pore; E=3-locular pore; F=microtubular duct; H=cruciform pore; J=antenna; L=claw; N=flagellate seta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7441381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

